## Additional Terms for Drilling Industry Usage

While this software is provided under the MIT License allowing broad usage,
users in the oil and gas industry should note:

### Professional Use Disclaimer
This software is intended for educational and analysis purposes. For
safety-critical drilling operations, users should:

- Validate calculations against established industry software
- Follow company-specific quality assurance procedures
- Comply with local regulatory requirements
- Use qualified personnel for interpretation of results

### Industry Standards Compliance
The calculations implemented in this software follow industry-standard
methods including:
- ISCWSA (Industry Steering Committee for Wellbore Survey Accuracy) guidelines
- SPE (Society of Petroleum Engineers) recommended practices
- Minimum curvature method as specified in drilling engineering literature

### Data Security
Users are responsible for ensuring compliance with:
- Company data security policies
- Regulatory requirements for well data handling
- Export control regulations where applicable

### Third-Party Dependencies
This software utilizes the following open-source libraries:
- Streamlit (Apache 2.0 License)
- Polars (MIT License)
- Plotly (MIT License)

Users should review the licenses of these dependencies for complete
legal compliance.
